# BioSense — State

**Date:** after completion of prerequisite tasks  
**Version:** 0.1.0  
**Status:** 🟡 In Development

## Goals & Tasks

**Primary Goal:** Develop a biological data monitoring and analysis system for medical research, enabling real-time anomaly detection and predictive insights.

**Key Objectives (with priorities and deadlines):**

| Objective | Priority | Deadline |
|-----------|----------|----------|
| Design and implement data ingestion pipeline (supports HL7 FHIR, CSV, JSON) | P0 | after completion of prerequisite tasks |
| Build core ML models for anomaly detection (vital signs, lab results) | P1 | after completion of prerequisite tasks |
| Develop user dashboard (real-time visualization, alerts) | P2 | after completion of prerequisite tasks |
| Integrate with hospital EMR systems (pilot) | P1 | after completion of prerequisite tasks |
| Conduct clinical validation study with 100+ patients | P2 | after completion of prerequisite tasks |
| Achieve HIPAA/GDPR compliance certification | P0 | after completion of prerequisite tasks |

## Current Phase

- Project initialization: defining architecture, assembling team, and setting up development infrastructure.
- Core documentation (README, LICENSE, STATE) completed. Concept document in progress.

